==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wollastonite
<hw>Wol"las*ton*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[After Dr.
<person>W. H. <etsep>Wollaston</etsep></person>, an English chemist, who
died in 1828.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A silicate of lime of a
white to gray, red, or yellow color, occurring generally in cleavable
masses, rarely in tabular crystals; tabular spar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wollaston's doublet</ent>⟦br⟧
